<div class="editor-left-col" id="recent-news">
<h1>What's New</h1>
<ul><li><a href="/news/blueberrysurvey">Scotland looks to blueberry hills</a></li><span><p>Scottish berries are famed for being among the best in the world so researchers are hoping canny Scots consumers can help them grow the best blueberries around.</p>
</span><li><a href="/news/wellcomeaward">Striking science lights up photography</a></li><span><p>A striking image that looks like a vision from a science fiction movie but is in fact a growing plant stem has won a Special Award in the 2011 Wellcome Image Awards for an SCRI scientist.</p>
</span><li><a href="/news/pip2011_fieldbookings">Field plots at Potatoes in Practice 2011</a></li><span><p>Potential exhibitors at Potatoes in Practice 2011 are reminded that field plot bookings must be submitted by 3 March for this year's event. It will be held at Balruddery Farm on Thursday 11 August 2011.</p>
</span></ul></div>
<div id="events" class="editor-right-col"><span class="hide">DO NOT EDIT ABOVE THIS POINT</span>
<h1>SCRI Website Membership</h1>
<h2>You are not logged in</h2><p class="account"><a href="/user/login?destination=node%2F8">Members Login</a> | <a href="user/register" title="Register on the SCRI site">Register</a></p><p>Joining the SCRI website enables you to make the most of your visit. Being a member means you can:</p>
<ul class="homepage">
    <li>Comment on news items.</li>
</ul>
<p>SCRI website members can also subscribe to our email bulletins:</p>
<ul class="homepage">
    <li>News</li>
    <li>Events.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> Membership is optional - registration is not required to read any section of the SCRI website.</p>
</div>
